    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Import your `custom.py` into your project.\r\n\r\n2. In `custom.py`, write the `move_or_turn(this_painter)` function. Inside your function:\r\n\r\n   * Write a `while` loop that runs while the `Painter` `is_facing_east()`\r\n   \r\n   * If the `Painter` `can_move()`, move forward one space\r\n   \r\n   * Else, call your `turn_right(this_painter)` function\r\n\r\n3. Save `custom.py` to your Backpack.\r\n\r\n4. In `main.py`, import the functions you need and help the `Painter` navigate around The Neighborhood.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/aa35e13e7400fcff961fb1b95e07e45b-choiceC.gif)",
